      <title>Climate Change, Environments Change, Works Change</title>
      <chapter>
        <paragraph>One primary impact of climate change in high-risk countries will be rising volatility in agricultural production, which will disrupt traditional farming, fishing and pastoral communities. Ecological disruption will in turn upend related industries down the production chain, undermining logistics and retail markets.</paragraph>
        <paragraph>Then comes the human fallout: by choice or out of desperation, many displaced rural people will turn to wage work or start ad-hoc businesses. Researchers found that in Indonesia, sea level rise will drive displacement of more than 80,000 farmers. These will led to massive migrations of people searching for jobs.</paragraph>
      </chapter>
