      <title>Sending Money Home</title>
      <chapter>
        <title>The Remittance</title>
        <paragraph>It is a transfer of money by a foreign worker to an individual in his or her home country. Money sent home by migrants competes with international aid as one of the largest financial inflows to developing countries. Workers' remittances are a significant part of international capital flows, especially with regard to labour-exporting countries.</paragraph>
